[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=ef28204&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=ef28204&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2837&quot; title=&quot;Fully asynchronous logging results in two disruptors being created&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-2837&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-2837&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Disruptor and JUL no longer recursively start the AsyncLoggerDisruptor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Previously logging initialization would result in an AsyncLoggerContext&lt;br/&gt;
initializing an AsyncLoggerDisruptor, which would access a logger from&lt;br/&gt;
JUL, starting the process again. This change avoids recursive calls with&lt;br/&gt;
a state check.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
